item.description:
To enable bash autocompletion, create a file with the following:
#! /bin/bash : ${PROG:=$(basename ${BASH_SOURCE})} _cli_bash_autocomplete() { local cur opts base COMPREPLY=() cur=&quot;${COMP_WORDS[COMP_CWORD]}&quot; opts=$( ${COMP_WORDS[@]:0:$COMP_CWORD} --generate-bash-completion ) COMPREPLY=( $(compgen -W &quot;${opts}&quot; -- ${cur}) ) return 0 } complete -F _cli_bash_autocomplete $PROG  Then source it from your bash profile
PROG=edward source FILE  Alternatively, name the file edward and place it in your system appropriate bash_completion.d/ directory.
